    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Broad-brimmed felt hats with strings on opposing sides bearing a formation of 15 tassels each. Red galeros are worn by cardinals in the Roman Catholic Church, while other colors may signify clergy of other ranks.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
